  02 Feb 2006; Marius Mauch <genone@gentoo.org> portage-2.1_pre4-r1.ebuild:
  Bump pycrpyto dep for ia64 (bug #121182)..

  29 Jan 2006; Jason Stubbs <jstubbs@gentoo.org>
  +portage-2.1_pre4-r1.ebuild:
  Regression fix for ebuilds that use or deps without a default atom.
  Also specifying version on pycrypto due to amd64 issues.

  28 Jan 2006; Jason Stubbs <jstubbs@gentoo.org>
  Add pycrypto dependency to 2.1_pre4.

*portage-2.1_pre4 (28 Jan 2006)

  28 Jan 2006; Jason Stubbs <jstubbs@gentoo.org>
  +portage-2.1_pre4.ebuild:
  Bug fix release for 2.1.

  23 Jan 2006; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Stable on hppa (bug #108262).

  22 Jan 2006; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha.

  21 Jan 2006; Michael Hanselmann <hansmi@gentoo.org> portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc.

  20 Jan 2006; Luis Medinas <metalgod@gentoo.org> portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64. See bug #108262.

  20 Jan 2006; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64; bug #108262

  20 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Marking stable on x86 wrt bug #108262.

  20 Jan 2006; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org> portage-2.0.54.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc wrt #108262

  20 Jan 2006; Jason Stubbs <jstubbs@gentoo.org>
  portage-2.0.53.ebuild, portage-2.0.54.ebuild, portage-2.1_pre3.ebuild:
  Moving portage-manpages dependency from PDEPEND to RDEPEND as there's no
  specific need for it to be installed after portage and is triggering a
  long-standing bug.

  01 Jan 2006; Jason Stubbs <jstubbs@gentoo.org>
  portage-2.1_pre3-r1.ebuild:
  Interim fix for xterm titles leaking to the terminal.

  31 Dec 2005; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org>
  portage-2.0.51.22-r3.ebuild, portage-2.0.53.ebuild, portage-2.0.54.ebuild,
  portage-2.1_pre3.ebuild:
  Pull in portage-manpages automagically via USE=doc.

